    "version": "18.3.30",There it is - `@types/react-router` has `@types/react@17` nested inside, while the top-level is `@types/react@18`. This causes the JSX element type mismatch. The fix is to force all `@types/react` references to resolve to the top-level version using `resolutions` in `package.json`:
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  ▸ edit
    path package.json
    before:   "engines": {
    "node": ">=18.x"
  }
    after:   "resolutions": {
    "@types/react": "^18.3.0"
  },
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18.x"
  }

